 You can enable the viewer cam feature from your\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.screenleap.com\/account\/settings\">Settings &amp; Preferences<\/a>. You can hide the viewer cam during your screen share by clicking on it.<\/p>\n<p>The viewer cam feature is currently only available for the Screenleap for Mac app, but it will be added to the Screenleap for Windows app in the near future.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We are excited to announce the general availability of the viewer cam feature for customers using the Screenleap for Mac app. The viewer cam is a small screen that appears below the\u00a0control panel when a viewer starts viewing your screen. It allows\u00a0your presentations to run more smoothly by giving you a real-time view of what [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[199],"class_list":["post-1431","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-screenleap","tag-screenleap"],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1431","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1431"}],"version-history":[{"count":18,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1431\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1451,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1431\/revisions\/1451"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.sc